---
import DocLayout from "../../../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import ApiEntry from "../../../../components/docs/ApiEntry.astro";
import Example from "../../../../components/docs/Example.astro";
---

<DocLayout
  title="openpress-create-slide"
  eyebrow="Skill"
  description="Create OpenPress slide decks with slide Press Tree generation, DeckSlide, slide layouts, reusable UI primitives, deck structure, and first-pass theme."
>
  <ApiEntry
    name="openpress-create-slide"
    kind="skill"
    importFrom="skills/openpress-create-slide/SKILL.md"
    summary="Owns slide artifact creation. It handles fresh workspace bootstrap when needed, adding a slide Press, DeckSlide/layout/ui source structure, theme intake, deck roles, assets, motion discipline, and verification."
  >
    <p>
      Use this when the artifact is a presentation or slide deck. The <code>openpress</code> skill
      still owns CLI lifecycle, validation, render, PDF/image export, upgrade, and migrate.
    </p>
  </ApiEntry>

  <h2>Workflow</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Check Node, npm, and npx. OpenPress requires Node.js 20 or newer.</li>
    <li>Detect fresh workspace vs existing <code>&lt;Workspace&gt;</code>.</li>
    <li>Gather topic, audience, title, slide count, density, motion, visual direction, assets, and slug.</li>
    <li>Create a slide Press with <code>type="slides"</code> and <code>page="slide-16-9"</code> by default.</li>
    <li>Generate <code>DeckSlide</code>, <code>layouts/</code>, and <code>ui/</code>.</li>
    <li>Import per-deck CSS from the deck entry and run <code>npm run build</code>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Default shape</h2>

  <Example title="Slide Press" language="tsx" code={`<Press slug="slide" title="Deck Title" type="slides" page="slide-16-9">
  <TitleSlide id="cover" title="Deck Title">
    <TitleSlide.Title objectId="title">Deck Title</TitleSlide.Title>
    <TitleSlide.Description objectId="description">
      One-line audience promise.
    </TitleSlide.Description>
  </TitleSlide>

  <TitledContentSlide id="problem-context" title="Problem Context">
    <TitledContentSlide.Eyebrow objectId="eyebrow">Context</TitledContentSlide.Eyebrow>
    <TitledContentSlide.Title objectId="title">Problem Context</TitledContentSlide.Title>
    <TitledContentSlide.Content>
      <Text as="p" objectId="summary">Write visible slide content directly in JSX.</Text>
    </TitledContentSlide.Content>
  </TitledContentSlide>
</Press>`} />

  <Example title="DeckSlide" language="tsx" code={`export function DeckSlide({ id, variant, title, children }) {
  return (
    <Slide
      id={id}
      title={title}
      className={\`op-slide op-slide--\${variant}\`}
    >
      <div className="op-slide__surface">
        <main className="op-slide__content">{children}</main>
        <footer className="op-slide__footer">
          <PageFolio variant="slash" currentFormat="2-digit" totalFormat="2-digit" />
        </footer>
      </div>
    </Slide>
  );
}`} />

  <h2>Layout and UI Boundary</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><code>components/</code> holds deck-level wrappers such as <code>DeckSlide</code>.</li>
    <li><code>layouts/</code> holds full-slide layouts such as <code>TitledContentSlide</code> and <code>ChapterOpenerSlide</code>.</li>
    <li><code>ui/</code> holds reusable content primitives such as <code>Timeline</code>, <code>KpiCard</code>, and <code>ImageFrame</code>.</li>
    <li>Text-backed compound slots should pass <code>TextProps</code> through to <code>Text</code> and use <code>objectId</code> on visible literal text for inline edit source mapping.</li>
    <li>Default output should compose visible content inline inside layout slots, not hide every slide behind a one-off component.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Page folio</h2>

  <p>
    Slide layouts should use <code>PageFolio</code> instead of hardcoded page numbers.
    The export pipeline resolves the final frame order, so the same component works in reader,
    PDF, and image export.
  </p>

  <Example title="Folio formats" language="tsx" code={`<PageFolio currentFormat="2-digit" />
// 01

<PageFolio variant="slash" currentFormat="2-digit" totalFormat="2-digit" />
// 04 / 35

<PageFolio variant="prefix" prefix="p " />
// p 4`} />

  <h2>Boundary</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Does not create reports, books, proposals, or other page-based artifacts. Use <code>openpress-create-pages</code>.</li>
    <li>Does not run upgrade or migration through create. Use <code>openpress</code>.</li>
    <li>Does not deploy. Use <code>openpress-deploy</code> after explicit user confirmation.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Source</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/quan0715/open-press/blob/main/skills/openpress-create-slide/SKILL.md" rel="noopener"><code>skills/openpress-create-slide/SKILL.md</code></a></li>
  </ul>
</DocLayout>
